The paper discusses image retrieval, which is a topic in computer vision and machine learning. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses representation and ranking of images, which are topics in information retrieval, making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) another likely sub-category. The use of nonnegative matrix factorization and contextual similarity learning suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the use of a large-scale image database suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia).
